<CAPTION>  Photo; PHOTO: From pop acts at the Great America amusement park to classic
charm at the classy Carmel Bach Festival, the Bay Area and central coast are
alive with music this summer. But steering clear of the crush for seats takes
some skill.  </CAPTION>
<DESCRIPT>  ENTERTAINMENT; SHOW; SALE; GUIDELINE  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  EACH of the special summer attractions in the South Bay and outlying areas has
its own way of marketing tickets. Get to know the landscape, and you'll have a
better chance at the concerts, seats and prices you want.;    (check) Paul
Masson Summer Series: This year the Paul Masson series is selling its tickets
through BASS. However if you buy your tickets in person from the BASS outlet
at 29 N. San Pedro St., San Jose, there's no service charge. The box office is
open 10 a.m. to 2 p.m. Monday through Friday.  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Arts &amp; Books  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  A FESTIVAL OF MUSICAL CHAIRS  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  Cover Story
See related stories pages 3, 12, and 13 of this section.  </MEMO>
<TEXT>     If you already have some Paul Masson tickets and can get into the venue,
the Paul Masson box office is open for walk-up sales during performances and
there's no service charge.;    Paul Masson sells many of its tickets by mail
order before the season begins. To get on the mailing list for next year's
performances, send a post card with your name and address to P.O. Box 1852,
Saratoga, 95070.;    For recorded ticket information, call (408) 741-5181.;   
(check) Villa Montalvo: Villa Montalvo charges $3 per order for handling phone
or mail orders. There's no charge if you buy tickets at the box office, 15400
Montalvo Road, Saratoga. The box office is open 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. Monday
through Saturday and 1 p.m. to 4 p.m. Sundays. It's also open before some
performances.;    Tickets for shows that have not sold out are available at
the door, and if shows do sell out early, Villa Montalvo sometimes sets up two
sets of bleachers on either side of the stage that are discounted about 25
percent. The bleacher seats usually go on sale about a week before the show.; 
  Finally, members of the non-profit Villa Montalvo get a 10 percent discount
on tickets. Call the box office, (408) 741-3428, for more information.;   
(check) Great America: The Santa Clara amusement park sells tickets during
operating hours for its concerts at the park.;    To get into a concert, you
have to buy an admission ticket. Great America has promotional deals with M&amp;M
Mars candy through July 31 (bring a Mars candy wrapper and get $4 off) and
with Longs Drugs Aug. 1 through Sept. 2 (pick up a voucher at the drug stores
good for $3 off).;    The park also has group sales plans. Call (408) 988-1800
for recorded information.;    (check) Cabrillo Music Festival: There's no
service charge for festival tickets bought at the door of the Santa Cruz Civic
Auditorium. The service charge for advance tickets bought at the auditorium's
box office or by phone is $1 per ticket. The box office, on the corner of
Center and Church streets, is open 9 a.m. to 6 p.m. Monday through Friday and
10 a.m. to 2 p.m. Saturday and Sunday.;    Subscription holders save 10
percent on single-ticket prices. Students and seniors get discounts, too. Call
the box office at (408) 429-3444.;    (check) Shoreline Amphitheatre:
Shoreline Amphitheatre has its own box office directly under the marquee at
the Mountain View concert venue. There's no service charge if you buy tickets
at the box office in person. Hours are 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. Monday through Friday
and on some weekends when major shows go on sale. The box office does not
accept checks, nor does it take phone orders. Call (415) 967-4040 for recorded
information.;    For some big shows, the box office opens a day ahead of time
offering limited tickets for Mountain View residents. You must have a
Shoreline ID card, available at the box office from 10 a.m. to 6 p.m.
weekdays, and another form of ID with your Mountain View address. For recorded
information on upcoming shows and pre-sale tickets, call (415) 968-6862.;   
(check) Carmel Bach Festival: You can buy tickets in person at the festival's
office in Room 11, Sunset Center (corner of San Carlos and Ninth streets),
Carmel.;    But since not all of us can be in Carmel, the festival charges $2
per order to take phone or fax orders. Call (408) 624-1521 for general
information, (408) 624-2788 to fax.;    (check) Shakespeare Santa Cruz:
Starting Monday, you can buy your tickets at the University of California,
Santa Cruz, Performing Arts Center box office and pay no service charge. Hours
are 11 a.m. to 6 p.m. Monday through Friday. The box office will be open
during weekend and evening shows starting July 20.;    There's a $2 per order
charge to get tickets by phone. Call (408) 459-4168 for information.;   
Shakespeare Santa Cruz has four subscription plans that save up to 21 percent
off single ticket prices. The group also offers student, senior and group
discounts.  </TEXT>
